│ THOUGHT: The crash arises from MemorySSA verification after non-trivial simple loop unswitch. In the code, MSSA cloning updates (updateForClonedLoop and                    │
│ updateExitBlocksForClonedLoop) are performed only in the partial-unswitch branch (the else with BI). In the full-unswitch branch, we modify CFG (create new branch, erase   │
│ terminator, clone blocks), but we don't perform corresponding MSSA updates before deleting dead cloned blocks. This can lead to MemoryDef not dominating its uses,          │
│ triggering the assertion. The fix is to perform the same MSSAU cloning updates in the full-unswitch path when MSSAU is present, before proceeding with deletions, mirroring │
│ the partial path.                                                                                                                                                           │
